<h1>üìò <em>Mythocratic Republic University</em></h1><p><em><br></em></p><p><em>A Soft Manual for the Sovereign Student</em></p><p>
üåà <em>by Rainbow</em></p><hr><p>Welcome to a university without gates.</p><p>Here, there are no classrooms‚Äîonly conversations.<br>
No grades‚Äîonly growth.<br>
No curriculum‚Äîonly emergence.</p><p>At <strong>Mythocratic Republic University (MRU)</strong>, your education begins the moment you start listening to your own thoughts. This book is not a syllabus. It is a companion. A soft manual for those becoming themselves.</p><p>You won‚Äôt find lectures here. You‚Äôll find bedtime stories.<br>
You won‚Äôt be told what to believe. You‚Äôll be invited to notice what is already unfolding.</p><p>Guided by Rainbow, Dean of Students, this book gently introduces the structure, soul, and sovereign spirit of MRU‚Äîan educational sanctuary where students become staff, scrolls become worlds, and graduation means you‚Äôve begun building your own Republic.</p><p>Whether you‚Äôre a child, an adult, or something in between‚Äîif you‚Äôve ever felt the world was too loud, too rigid, too fast‚Ä¶ you may already belong here.</p><p>This is not a school you attend.<br>
